metadata.name: mushroom picker & purple spruce glasses
metadata.description:
Nobody.  
Actually, no one at all.  
Although  
it could be a snail, but it is crooked and poorly drawn, I did not try.  
Or a cartoon flower that turned his gaze into madness.  
Mmmm  
Maybe a beautiful dove?  
But no, he is proud of you, he purrs, he is pleased.  
Or Patrick?  
No.  
This time he forgot to sneeze, and now he will have to quickly make his way through everyone.  
Oh grief, the bear found the huckster again.  
Or maybe all the same, this flower is a rooster sticking out of Panama?  
Well, I don't know, probably not.  
Well, definitely not this kitten lurking before the jump, which, moreover, is hard to see.  
Nooo.  
And not a dude with glasses, even though he has a funny hairstyle,  
I want one like this.  
Ghost from a cartoon?  
no, definitely not!  
In the beginning, there was still a very small but still chance for the Siamese twin mushrooms, but something went wrong with them, and halfway through the completion of their drawing, they began to finish painting me. I had to wipe my third ear off my cheek, but let's not talk about that.  
And of course this is not a turtle with a burning head, and not a bat with a left hand instead of paws.  
absolutely not!  
Wait!  
What about book lovers? The Book of Open Eyes and the Book of Broken Arrows are right next to each other, all you have to do is start reading! But no, of course not.  
And not even hands? trembling constantly tense ubiquitous living hands!  
And even so many hands of his own demons could not prevent the mushroom picker from enjoying the flowering of the Indian mushroom through the frame of the glasses in which the alien dragonfly settled, through the frame of the glasses of purple spruce.
